Package: torontodown
Title: An R Markdown thesis template for University of Toronto using the bookdown package
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(person(c("Matthew", "T."), "Warkentin", email = "matt.warkentin@mail.utoronto.ca", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Francois", "Pitt", email = "fpitt@cs.utoronto.ca", role = c("aut", "ccp")))
Description: Using the bookdown package and LaTeX thesis templates from
    University of Toronto, this package aims to encourage reproducible research using
    simple Markdown syntax while embedding all of the R code to produce plots
    and analyses as well. This package is based on Chester Ismay's thesisdown and Zhian Kavmar's beaverdown.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5),
    knitr,
    bookdown
Imports: 
    yaml,
    fs,
    glue,
    here,
    stringr,
    clipr,
    cli,
    rstudioapi,
    assertthat
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/mattwarkentin/torontodown
BugReports: https://github.com/mattwarkentin/torontodown/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
SystemRequirements: pandoc (>= 1.18) - http://pandoc.org
RoxygenNote: 7.0.2
